        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Not sure yet if I like it myself, but just throwing it out an idea: A possibility could be for a plugin to be able to allocate a separate buffer handle for the same buffer, with which api methods could be called with more \"privileges\", like mutating a read-only buffer with `set_lines`. While it still might be possible for other plugins or the user to get hold of this handle, this would still reduce the change that a plugin-owned buffer gets mutated by others by _mistake_. In most cases I would expect a plugin to to create a buffer, create this handle (by some API function), and set the buffer as read-only. A good-behaving plugin should never \"take ownership\" of an existing buffer in this way unless explicitly asked by the user.\n",
