            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> While it still might be possible for other plugins or the user to get hold of this handle, this would still reduce the change that a plugin-owned buffer gets mutated by others by mistake.\n\nYeah, I noticed that Vim8's special \"job\" type achieves that: by making job handles a special type, plugin jobs are implicitly \"namespaced\", and accidental conflict with other plugins is eliminated.\n\nNot sure I like special types nor ACLs/privilege management though. Would prefer a combination of \"passive\" flagging (like `:verbose`) and explicit overrides (temporarily set/unset options for a given atomic request).\n",
