        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Good point, it's not as common as I assumed. \n\nInstead of buffer ownership, given that option set/unset operations are already quasi-tracked, we could track \"ownership\" of `'modifiable'` (and other options) instead of ownership of the buffer.\n\nOn the other hand, if this is not a common operation, the verbosity of something like `nvim_set_options_atomic` seems justifiable and preferrable: rather than have some alternative universe of privileges (cognitive overhead), just offer this explicit sugar.\n\nNote that `nvim_set_options_atomic` (or whatever we call it) is a long-awaited feature: it will avoid the try-finally dance of saving/restoring options, which is a very common pattern in Vim and VimL.\n",
            "created_at": "2016-10-22T12:09:48Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/5486#issuecomment-255524823",
